race.description: Wild West Bundaberg Rum Precinct 28/02 Mdn Plate
race.comment: RING OF FIRE (8) sets up nicely for this fourth-up after working home nicely into second at the Sapphire Coast. McDougall sticks and he's ready to get off the mark. Looks the one to beat, though BRAVO SIX (6) has been a flashing light in his two runs and should be hitting his straps now. Loses McDougall but has plenty of scope for further improvement at start three. LAUNCH MODE (4) finds the maiden win elusive but has run littered through his form that can measure up. The 3kg claim gets him in well. Worth keeping safe. SEASMOKE (12) was much better at the latest when on speed at Albury. Drawn less kind this time but is worth some thought.
